An adapter to the interface TraverseAction.

All the implemented methods do nothing else than exist, i.e. the method bodies are all empty. User defined traverse actions can be provided by overriding the appropriate methods.

For each traversable JSOM type there is a pair of methods called performAction(...) and actionPerformed(...). The first method must be called as soon as a traversable JSOM object gets visited with the JSOM object itselfe as argument. Then all JSOM type members of the visited JSOM object must be travered. Finally the method actionPerformed(...) must be called with the same JSOM object as argument that has been passed to the performAction method.
